rain of problems from inside the clinic, these NPs were not only solving a broader set of concerns for their patients; they became a professional solution for managing "difficult people" for both their employer and the state. Through More Than Medicine, we discover that the problems found in the NP's exam room are as much a product of our nation's disinvestment in social problems as of physician scarcity or rising costs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGeriatric nursingxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aNurse practitionerszUnited States. 0aOlder African AmericansxCare. 0aOlder African AmericansxServices for. 0aSenior centerszUnited States. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aLabor History. 4aSocial Medicine. 7aMEDICAL / Hospital Administration & Care.2bisacsh  anursing, medicine, health, gender inequality, care work.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070480808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020z9783110704600oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501748172zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501748172423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501748172/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070480-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishb2020